
[1]disquietude

   DISQUIETUDE, n. Want of peace or tranquility; uneasiness; disturbance;
   agitation; anxiety. It is, I believe, most frequently used of the mind.

   Religion is our best security from the disquietudes that embitter life.
     __________________________________________________________________

